  "title": "Exploring Metaclasses",
  "lessonText": "Metaclasses are a powerful aspect of Python that allow you to control class creation.",
  "data": {
    "content": "## Key Points on Metaclasses\n- Metaclasses define the behavior of classes.\n- They are classes of a class.\n- You can customize class creation using `__new__` and `__init__` methods.\n- Common use cases include enforcing coding standards and modifying class attributes.\n- Use `type` or define a custom metaclass by inheriting from `type`."
  }
}
